{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Progress (investigation + fix):\n\nROOT CAUSE CONFIRMED (discriminating experiment on git 2.54): git >= 2.47's detached\n`git maintenance run --auto` (repack --cruft --write-midx) runs OUTSIDE rebar's write lock,\nracing concurrent writers on the shared linked-worktree object DB -> corruption (invalid\nobject / Error building trees) -> dropped writes. rebar's own lock is sound (0 overlaps).\nDiscriminator: control 8/20 losses; maintenance.auto=false -> 0/20; autoDetach=false -> 0/20.\ngc.auto=0 does NOT fix it (git >= 2.47 gates on maintenance.auto, not gc.auto) — which is why\nprior fixes (4c1c index self-heal; WU-1 gc.autoDetach=true) missed it.\n\nUNBLOCK: temporary skip of the failing test landed on main as Gerrit change 768 (MERGED).\n\nFIX (approach chosen by operator = foreground maintenance, preserves WU-1 bounded-growth):\n`_gc_config_unit` now sets `--unset gc.auto` + `gc.autoDetach=false` + `maintenance.autoDetach\n=false` so a triggered repack runs FOREGROUND, serialized under the write lock. Skip removed\n(test re-enabled). Updated: test_gc_config.py, test_ensure_drift_matrix.py, sync.py +\nconcurrency.md + init.py docstrings (corrected the \"gc safe by construction\" claim). New ADR\n0051 documents the decision + measured perf.\n\nPERF (operator-approved): foreground repack pause ~0.16s @2k objects, ~2s @10k, ~0.2ms/object;\nfires ~every 1,700 commits; global write pause while it runs; reads unaffected; scaling\nceiling = 60s lock budget (~300k+ objects). Escape hatch = disable auto-maint + serialized\n`git maintenance run --task=gc`.\n\nSTATUS: RED->GREEN + mutation verification running on git 2.54; then push to Gerrit."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784322493179662001,"uuid":"12ef7312-84a7-4804-b4b5-e2500cd018a9"}